summary: The balls of Nintendo
body:
The balls of Nintendo

Are made of something far stronger than steel. The insanity of handing one of your largest franchises over to an indie team to make your new spinoff is through the fucking roof. I don’t know what PR person/developer/executive convinced everyone that this was the right decision, but I would like to see more oddball titles like Cadence of Hyrule going forward. Do this with Metroid. Do this with Mario. Hand others the keys to make more weird and wonderful titles.

summary: MICROSOFT SAYS NO XBOX LIVE SDK FOR SWITCH AS OF NOW, BUT EXPECT MORE XBOX LIVE-ENABLED TITLES OVER THE NEXT YEAR
title: MICROSOFT SAYS NO XBOX LIVE SDK FOR SWITCH AS OF NOW, BUT EXPECT MORE XBOX LIVE-ENABLED TITLES OVER THE NEXT YEAR
body:
Can Microsfot and Nintendo get any closer? The friendship really started to grow through Minecraft, and things have truly blossomed since then. That exciting collaboration continues with Cuphead, which was revealed for Switch earlier today. That’s not the only title the two will be teaming up for, either.

During a GDC panel, Microsoft talked a bit about Xbox Live. While they said there’s no Xbox Live SDK for Switch at the moment, more collabs like Cuphead are on the way. Microsoft says to expect more Xbox Live-enabled titles to hit the platform throughout the next year.

summary: V-RALLY 4 - TWO MORE JAPANESE TRAILERS
title: V-RALLY 4 - TWO MORE JAPANESE TRAILERS
body:
The legendary off-road racing game returns! Enjoy an extreme experience while becoming an expert in a demanding simulation. Take on the challenges of rallies, rallycross, drifts, buggies and hill climbs, and set off on a spectacular journey across every continent.

V-Rally 4 hits Japan on April 11th, 2019, and is priced at ¥8,424.

summary: FDG ENTERTAINMENT SELLS OVER 200K GAMES ON SWITCH
title: FDG ENTERTAINMENT SELLS OVER 200K GAMES ON SWITCH
body: FDG Entertainment has a major reason to celebrate. The company decided to support Switch long ago, and that decision paid off. The company says that they’ve now sold over 200k units of Switch games worldwide! With fantastic titles like Blossom Tales and Monster Boy and the Cursed Kingdom in their library, I’d say they deserve every bit of their success!
